Problem Statement
1. The Bin Packing problem involves packing a set of items of different sizes into a
minimum number of bins, where each bin has a fixed capacity.
2. Each item must be placed in exactly one bin, and the total size of items in a bin
must not exceed the bin capacity.
Types of Bin Packing Algorithms
1. First Fit: When processing the next item, scan the exisƟng bins in order and place
the item in the first bin that has enough remaining space. If the item does not fit
in any exisƟng bin, open a new bin and place the item there.
2. Best Fit: When processing the next item, place it in the bin that will leave the
least remaining empty space aŌer placement. If no exisƟng bin can accommodate
the item, create a new bin.
3. Next Fit: When processing the next item, check whether it fits in the current bin
(the bin used for the previous item). If it fits, place it in the same bin. Otherwise,
close the current bin and open a new bin.
Algorithm Idea
First Fit Place item in the first bin that fits
Best Fit Place item where leŌover space is minimum
Next Fit Try current bin, otherwise open new bin
Complexity Analysis
- SorƟng items (Decreasing order): O(n log n)
- Bin placement (First Fit): O(n²) (worst case)
- Overall Time Complexity: O(n²)
- Space Complexity: O(n)
